			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I'd just like to say, you're down right wrong.<BR>
<BR>
     First off, Halflings have better STR, STA, and DEX than Wood Elves.  They have equal AGI and WIS.  Halflings too start off with the abilities, infravision, and hide.  However, Halflings also have the ability to sneak.  As to the foraging arguement, all druids get forage at lvl 5.<BR>
     The only thing Wood Elves have over Halflings is INT and CHA.  However, these stats don't matter.  INT isn't nearly low enough to make a difference.  I can still get my skills up faster than any of my friends with high INT.  Besides, when you get to higher levels, your skills go up faster than you level anyway.  That all means that INT is not important.  Neither is CHA.  The only things I sell/buy from merchants are inexpensive iteams anyway.  The low CHA doesn't make more of a difference than a few silver.  I sell/buy most of my stuff from other players.  If there is something I have to buy from a merchant, and it costs ALOT, then I can get a pretty High Elf to buy it for me.  I simply give her the money for it.  <BR>
<BR>
I think MY point has been proven.
				</font>
